 <title>AllJoyn 14.06 is Here! Focus on Security and Performance Improvements </title>
 <link>https://identity.allseenalliance.org/news/blogs/2014/07/alljoyn-1406-here-focus-security-and-performance-improvements</link>
 <description>
		&lt;span class=&quot;a2a_kit a2a_target addtoany_list&quot; id=&quot;da2a_2&quot;&gt;
			&lt;a class=&quot;a2a_button_facebook&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a class=&quot;a2a_button_twitter&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a class=&quot;a2a_button_google_plus&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;a2a_dd addtoany_share_save&quot; href=&quot;http://www.addtoany.com/share_save#url=https%3A%2F%2Fidentity.allseenalliance.org%2Fnews%2Fblogs%2F2014%2F07%2Falljoyn-1406-here-focus-security-and-performance-improvements&amp;amp;title=Blogs%20-%20AllSeen%20Alliance&quot;&gt; Share&lt;/a&gt;
		&lt;/span&gt;
		
		
  &lt;div class=&quot;field-body view-mode-rss&quot;&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;I’ve been in the software field for more than 30 years, and I must say I’ve seen few things more exciting than what’s happening just six months since the AllSeen Alliance was created. We now have 50 members hard at work expanding the &lt;a href=&quot;https://allseenalliance.org/developer-resources/alljoyn-open-source-project&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;AllJoyn&lt;/a&gt; open source Internet of Everything framework or building it into their products.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Most gratifying is seeing the community respond to the call for true Internet of Things (IoT) interoperability by &lt;em&gt;voting with their code&lt;/em&gt;. Members are devoting time, effort and creative energy to grow the framework and advance the widespread use of AllJoyn.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Today, we hit another milestone as the Alliance announces the release of AllJoyn, &lt;a href=&quot;https://allseenalliance.org/source-code&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Version 14.06&lt;/a&gt;, to further enable the ability to connect devices and systems across brands, transports, platforms and operating systems. This is the &lt;a href=&quot;https://allseenalliance.org/news/blogs/2014/03/open-source-framework-internet-everything-gets-update&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;second release &lt;/a&gt;since the Alliance’s formation in December. We’re on a fast-paced schedule that reflects the strong, collaborative interest within the community.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Version 14.06 is largely about improving overall security and performance of the AllJoyn framework as we scale to large networks of IoT devices ranging from embedded system microcontrollers running an RTOS to SmartTVs, home appliances, mobiles, tablets, PC’s and server class devices running high-level operating systems. The project now includes enhanced security algorithms using elliptic curve cryptography, new features simplifying M2M interactions, fast discovery with reliability, low power use and optimizations for publish/subscribe use cases such as sensors. This release also brings improved support for iOS developers. The result is significant performance improvements to overall network performance and the basis for the next stage in the evolution of the platform.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you’re wondering how developers can get involved, that’s easy: AllJoyn is an open source software framework project. Developers don’t have to be members of the AllSeen Alliance to make contributions. Open development means that anyone can get involved and contribute to the evolution of the codebase. The Alliance provides detailed information on&lt;a href=&quot;https://allseenalliance.org/developer-resources/how-to-participate&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt; how to make contributions&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Stay tuned as well for the scheduling of more AllSeen Alliance&lt;a href=&quot;https://allseenalliance.org/news/blogs/2014/04/we-re-throwing-hackfest-and-everyone-invited&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt; HackFests&lt;/a&gt; – intensive days of training labs, hands-on coding and fun. The first AllSeen HackFest took place May 1 in San Jose and went really well. More than 80 attendees received an introduction to AllJoyn and hands-on training for software and hardware integration with the project. As for making code contributions to AllJoyn, you don’t need to be an AllSeen Alliance member or have any previous connection to the group to participate.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;/div&gt;
</description>
 <pubDate>Tue, 01 Jul 2014 15:26:20 +0000</pubDate>
